There is no one liner command for this one, not without prior knowledge anyway.
First, we cd into the /etc/cron.d/ dir and cat some of the crontabs.
Since we are looking to go to level 22, any that are being used by bandit22 are of interest.
There is one script running at regular intervals, let's take a look at it.
Upon a cat of the script, it seems there is a random file in /tmp that is being written to regularly, and it contains the password for bandit22.
Doing a cat of that file gives the password.
